  "datePublished": "2025-12-31",
  "description": "Playing cards likely emerged through layered exchange rather than a single origin event. Early card-like media are usually traced through parts of Asia, then through Islamic regions, then into Europe, where local production and print culture stabilized durable deck formats. By the time cards became common in Europe, they were already both leisure objects and commercial goods.",
